##Wuhan more than 600 kilometers away, I in the county hospital to fight the epidemic

WMSYGSDR

Function introduction, each line has the earnest person, again the ordinary person also has the extraordinary story. Huazhong University of Science and Technology Press Official non-fiction story platform, the story of the people will meet here.

On the first night of the New Year, when I went to help, the protective gear I saw by my desk was everything I had left.

1

January 25,2020, the first afternoon of the New Year, I received a notice from the head nurse, night fever clinic to support the night shift. At the time, about a week after the COVID-19 outbreak, the city had just reported four confirmed cases.

I work for the hospital, in Wuhan to the East 600 km of the county, is the small county-level area is the only public second-class hospital, undertake the county's disease prevention and treatment work.

On January 21st, twenty-seven, the Wuhan epidemic began to ferment online, and the province had confirmed cases, and the news was overwhelming and Hung Up.

On January 22, twenty-eight, I was told that, as a member of the Emergency Response Team, my phone needed to be turned on 24 hours a day.

No one expected the outbreak to quickly spiral out of control. As early as a week ago, Corey's colleagues were still discussing the new year's schedule. Two newly married colleagues happened to be on the night shift in their thirties, beating their chests and lamenting their bad luck, but also can gnash one's teeth to adjust the time that reunites with family, arrive on time branch office takes over.

I was working the day shift when I got the notice in the afternoon of the 1st day. Put down the phone, I quickly and colleagues shift, colleagues know that I will go to support at night fever clinic, told me must protect themselves. Before leaving work, I went around to the infection department, which was outside the inpatient department, to prepare myself for the evening.

The infection department is in a separate three-story building, separated from the inpatient department by a river, and many people in masks head toward the fever clinic. At the door of the fever clinic, a nurse in a white protective suit, gloves and goggles was calling out the patient's name to arrange a visit. Two "heavily armed" doctors are seen in the exam room.

As I pushed forward, the nurse was just calling out a name. "Is that you? " She asked. "No, " I said. "I'm the night nurse. Where should I change? " She quickly got up, led me inside and led me up the stairs to the second floor, "Get the head nurse. "

At the nurses'station on the second floor, I didn't see the head nurse in the infection department, but I did see the head nurse. The director only wore a mask, to see me, hurriedly let to support the day shift rehabilitation section head nurse led me to find the way. The head nurse took me to recognize the road, send me out also did not forget to tell me, this time of many patients, must wear good protection measures at night, protect yourself.

On the way back, a steady stream of people wearing masks were moving in the same direction. I watched the endless stream of people in front of the fever clinic from afar. My heart sank and my mood sank.

After the outbreak of the epidemic, I have the fluky psychology at this moment nothing exists, overlaying the nest, how many eggs, the danger is really in the side.

2

When the fever clinic was first opened, the medical staff were all from the infection department. At the end of the day, the number of consultations was beyond imagination. The doctor on duty had not slept for more than 30 hours. The hospital urgently mobilized manpower from various departments to support the infection department.

The head nurse sent a message from the group: The COVID-19 is worse than we thought, we need to be on call, we need to be organized, my unit has already sent out the first wave of nurses to support us, and there is a long battle ahead, if we need more personnel, is the preparation class to go or individual active registration?

The day shift is usually reserved for the night shift nurse, and the night shift is reserved for the night shift nurse.

"Let me go, " I said in the group. "I'm single, I don't have any burden, and my psychological quality is OK. " Xiaoyan, the quality control nurse, said: "No way. You've already been there. I'll go next. " Tao said: "have a good rest when you get back. We'll go later. " Kobayashi said: "I'll go. If you have children, lean back. " Jun said: "If you don't have children, lean back. I'll go. "

It was a madhouse. At last, the head nurse made a decision to reserve the class for a short period of time. If it was a long period, she would choose another person and we would all obey the arrangement.

In another group, the director sent a chat record, is the department of Dr. Bei volunteered to fever clinic support, in the second day of the New Year after the shift in the Department of Hospitalization, will be stationed in the hospital, at any time.

Dr. Bei to support, in fact, is expected, he is good-tempered in the department, often patients come all the way to see him. There is an old man, as long as Dr. Pui help him, he said Dr. Pui good, for the sake of the patient, explained in detail, he helped himself to see a doctor at ease. Among the nurses, Dr. Bishop was also popular. "I was very busy on my first night shift, " Jun said. "Dr. Berman took my patient's temperature. "

Dr. Bay said in the group, follow-up section of the duty only a little bit harder, Corey was already short of staff, this is even more short. Without having to face each other, the atmosphere in the group felt a little grim, and Dr. Bey joked, I'm going to miss you all, and I'm going to be here when I get back.

Jun quickly replied in the following: When you come back, I invite you to eat the egg fried rice in the canteen. Tao Quips: Dr. Bei doesn't eat egg fried rice without meat. The atmosphere just livened up, someone immediately issued a sentence: that do not know the end of next month to eat to eat AH.

Group of instant solidification, half a day no reply, I thought, back to a "waiting for you to come back" , the bottom of the moment was "waiting for you to come back" screen. I put my phone down and tried to get some rest.

3

In order not to delay the shift, I arrived at the infection department half an hour early.

Midnight, the cold wind wrapped drizzle, in this cold night to fall, it is particularly cold. Wearing a Poncho and a big helmet, I followed the path I had explored in the afternoon until I reached the dressing room. Change into the nurse's uniform, before going out in order to keep warm attached to the warm baby fell on the ground, I tangled for a long time, or it was thrown into the garbage can.

At the nurses' station, two "heavily armed" nurses were changing shifts, and they gave me a suit of protective clothing and told me to put it on and go downstairs to the clinic to get a mask.

I asked them if they couldn't go to the bathroom in their Hazmat suits. They said, "No way. ". I'm struggling. What am I gonNA do. They said they had to go to the bathroom one time before getting dressed, and then they had to hold it in until they got off work. According to them, it shouldn't be too hard to go eight hours without eating or drinking. I had to do it.

Downstairs, the office is brightly lit and there are still many patients waiting in line. Thankfully, nearly all of them are wearing masks.

The doctor on duty is patient, the nurse is at the door to register the patient's details, including the specific address, ID number and fever date, whether Wuhan travel history or personal contact history has become the most important information.

The night nurse, who was arranging the appointments, wrapped so tightly that I couldn't identify the patient, approached her and said, I'm here to take over. She looked up, and I saw a white mist over her goggles, tiny droplets of water gathering and falling to one side. She said: It's twelve o'clock, how time flies, come quickly, I'll give you a mask.

I was still wearing my usual surgical mask, and she hurriedly led me to another room, took a small key from the upper cabinet, opened the locked drawer on the lower level, and counted the N95 masks that had been placed inside twice in front of me, "There are only a limited number of shifts and you have to register everyone. "

She handed me one and wrote down my name and number in front of me. On one side of the table, there are several sets of protective clothing, disposable hats, shoe covers, neatly placed on the stool, "gloves, hats, shoe covers, protective clothing, can be used. "

When I finished, I put on my mask and goggles and followed her back to the office. "You'll be in charge of collecting patient information, asking for basic medical history, arranging patient visits, and calling this number if you have any patients to observe. " She handed me a piece of paper, it had a number written on it.

When she finished, she picked up the register and went next door. "there were so many people in the queue, " she said. "A patient with a fever felt that the waiting time was too long

I waited in the exam room for a while. She came back with the register book and handed me a piece of paper. "He won't come back. I've got his name and number. You'll be on the day shift tomorrow. Make sure you track him. "

I nodded, knowing. She waved good-bye to me. "I have to go to the bathroom quickly. bye-bye. I'll go first. "

4

The room was not as noisy as it had been during the day, with feverish patients lining up at the door, checking stacks of medical records to see how long it would take them to get their turn.

As I closed my eyes in my suit and goggles, I found it difficult to breathe. The fog coated my glasses with white mist, and I struggled to identify the patient in front of me from the narrow, clear space, helping them calculate their waiting time, put the new patient outside.

It's not a good time. At one point, I counted out the first patient about two minutes before I called out the name of the next patient. While the patients in the back waited, the first few patients who had had blood tests and chest films inserted themselves into the room for a follow-up visit. A crowd of people surrounded the doctors so tightly that the patients in the back waited for more than ten minutes.

Later, I learn from experience, will follow-up patients in the hands of the test sheet, with first-time patients with the cross-call, the room suddenly empty a space. Whenever a patient goes in, I tell them to wait outside in the ventilation, it's more crowded, it's more dangerous. They're all GONNA walk away.

There are patients who want to see the doctor ahead of time. A 60-year-old uncle went in and out of the door several times. He looked through his medical records three times in five minutes. After hesitating for a while, he finally asked if he could give his wife a look in advance. The old man hunched in his chair in the corridor, wearing a thick cotton-padded jacket and a cotton-gauze mask. I opened her chart and recorded her temperature at the Emergency Room: 38.8 C.

After asking, I learned that the old man has a history of high blood pressure and bronchitis, at home tonight more than 7:00 consciously weak, a touch of forehead like a fever, this just rushed over. To the emergency room, the nurse a fever, let her come here first check, two people have been waiting for more than an hour.

I was a little embarrassed, waiting in the room patients, have or high or low fever, and wait a long time. On second thought, I gave the old man to retake the temperature, and talk to her to make sure the old man is in good spirits, so I decided to ask her to wait a little longer. The old man was understanding and said "thank you" to me in some embarrassment.

There were four patients in line before the old man. Twenty minutes later, when the doctor was about to see the old man, a young patient came into the room with a report card after a follow-up examination. I consulted with him, whether let the old man see a doctor first, the young man very readily agreed, back outside the door.

As the minutes ticked by and the number of patients waiting at the door slowly dwindled, I found that 70 per cent of the patients who came to see the doctor were young and middle-aged people under 40, with a low-grade fever that rarely exceeded 38 °C. Registration asked whether Wuhan Sojourn history or had contact with the relevant personnel, are very quick to answer, with a very high degree.

A family member, accompanied by me, spoke to me in a low, mysterious voice and asked me if there were any confirmed cases in the county. At that time I did not know that on the same morning, my hospital found a highly suspected case, has been sent to the city designated hospital, and he shook his head, said not yet heard. He smiled and told his wife that the house was safe.

Not just him, but everyone around me, myself included, thought the house was safe when the outbreak first started.

5

January 21, twenty-seven, I came back from the field of friends gathering, a few people talking about Wuhan Pneumonia, are relaxed. We firmly believe that home is a clean land, 2003 SARS, 14 years of avian flu, there are no cases, there is no reason to have this year.

Twenty-eight, after receiving a call for a 24 hour shift, I texted them: Better Watch out, I'm on call at the hospital.

Qingqing went to the street to buy a mask. She went to three stores and bought 20 pieces. She said in the group: Now can not grab a mask, the hospital has a mask?

The supply of face masks in hospitals is even tighter. Due to the large increase in the use of materials in the infection and emergency departments, the supply room is given priority to the first-line departments, and the inpatient department can only rely on inventory support. Head nurse from the beginning of the new year, every day to the staff to work, a mask can not be wasted.

From the news that masks were out of stock to the news that "who knows where to buy alcohol" , it took only 24 hours. On Jan. 23, the news that the city had been sealed in Wuhan rang like thunder, with a message saying that RT-Mart had been emptied of rice, flour and oil, and that even instant noodles were packed in boxes into shopping carts.

I asked my mother: Do we have any rice and vegetables at home? My mother said, there are enough for a month. I feel a little relieved, after work, could not help but be curious, went to the neighborhood at the door of the supermarket, found that the staff is a bag to the store to move rice, shelves are full of Dangdang, this thoroughly reassuring.

On January 26, the second day of the Lunar New Year, the city released the details of the confirmed patient. I now know that there has already been one case in the county. At the same time, I learned from the director's mouth that the patient is a migrant worker who returned from Wuhan. As soon as the CT images came out, they were basically confirmed, is being sequestered in the exam room. Fortunately, he entered the hospital after no one else met, the only possible infection of the attending doctor has been quarantined.

From time to time in different wechat groups, the news broke that a certain community had been isolated as a whole, each one true in contrast to the official announcement of the confirmed case.

Paying attention to official news became part of my daily routine, but there was no real tension. It wasn't until a viral image of a confirmed patient visiting the Golden Eagle on the 21st went viral on social media that I really panicked and tried to remember the last day I visited the Golden Eagle. To ensure that they are not infected with the possibility, I decided to thoroughly implement the hospital, home two point line policy, rest and recuperate.

Zhong Nanshan's suggestion was forwarded to friends repeatedly, reminding them not to visit each other during the Spring Festival and not to have dinner together. My friend Li Li came home from Shanghai to see her parents. She refused to go out to meet her. After two days without milk tea and rice noodles, she hurried back to Shanghai overnight.

On January 27, the third day of the Lunar New Year, every district in the county began to close its doors. Community cadres and property management staff dressed in volunteers'red vests and masks registered every vehicle entering and leaving the only open gate and persuaded everyone to wear masks.

My father used to go into the supermarket to buy some vegetables when he came home. I've been telling him to wear a mask since, and instead he's telling me I'm making a fuss. After returning home on the third day of the New Year, he looked defeated, and talked passionately about the scene when the supermarket staff refused to let him in. I am in a good mood, smiled for five minutes, gave him a mask, told him to go out every day must wear, "otherwise do not give you into the community. "

Zhang, the teacher in the department, used to invite her family to dinner on the fourth day of every year, before she wanted to change shifts with me, "if you take the fourth day off, help me go to work. " I waited until the fifth day when I saw her at work before I remembered the matter and hurried to ask her. Zhang Teacher said, the second day will be ordered to return the banquet, the deposit back, the hotel lost, are selling vegetables at the door.

On the fifth day, my colleague Xiao Chen drove back to her hometown to get the frozen ribs. She was stopped at the gate of the community. She immediately said, I'm not going in. She turned the bike around and waited at the intersection, while her father rode the battery out to deliver the ribs.

From the county to the countryside, staying at home consciously has become the latest moral code, not to add to the chaos of the country has also become the latest moral standard. From the 21st day shopping, almost no one on the street to almost all now wear masks, change only a few days.

-6 -

Since January 23, a number of hospitals in Wuhan have issued information to the public asking for help. When I opened the link, I found that the Wuhan frontline medical staff were running out of almost all the necessary materials, and it was hard to imagine what was keeping them in the ward.

Without a protective suit, Dr. Bay wore only a mask and a hat and sat through the third day of the Lunar New Year. Back to the ward after the heart palpitations, glad there are no suspected cases today, barely escaped a disaster.

It's a lie to say you're not afraid. It's a lie to say you're not working hard.

On the first night of the New Year, the doctor on duty at the fever clinic was a resident in the department of infection, surnamed Rong. From the fever clinic just opened on the Post, Ward Clinic both, energy and physical strength to reach the extreme.

At 6:15 in the morning, she watched the last patient with a fever and lay prone on her desk for a while before she got up on her feet. She hadn't moved since her shift began at 6 p.m. the night before, and had been cooped up in her hazmat suit for so long that she kept writing orders on her computer, and by the end of the night, she was almost face to face with the screen, to see the characters that pop out.

On the morning of the second day, when the next colleague appeared at the door, I was almost overjoyed, after the rapid handover, the first time to go to the toilet.

Only once experienced, I can better understand the colleagues in Wuhan, in what kind of purgatory inside, suffering what kind of torture.

Today, more and more medical teams from Hubei Province have been stationed in Wuhan Hospital to replace the exhausted front-line medical staff. Although thousands of miles away, but with the same anti-virus mood, January 28, I according to the full red fingerprint "please" leave their own share, I hope to do a little bit of help.

Are you afraid if I do draw you?

Afraid, not afraid. Everyone is afraid of death, it is human nature, but reason tells me not to be afraid, for I have the strength of the nation behind me.

So, shall we?

Of course. Small but big. All.

How do you say smaller?

It's my job. It's my life.

It's getting bigger?

If what I do serves the interests of my country, I will go at it even at the cost of my own life,.

(the characters appear to be pseudonyms.)
